# Global git ignore — applies to every repo via core.excludesfile.
# Managed by stow (linked to ~/.gitignore_global). Separate from this
# repo's own .gitignore, which only governs the dotfiles repository.
#
# Keep this list to things that are personal / machine- / tool-specific and
# would be noise in *any* project. Project-specific artifacts (node_modules,
# build output, etc.) belong in each project's own .gitignore, not here.

